## Silicon Carbide: A Compound That Grinds and Glows

"Carborundum" redirects here. Don't confuse it with [Corundum](/Corundum), though I suppose both sound like they belong in a dusty, forgotten laboratory.

### Silicon Carbide

A sample of silicon carbide, looking like a particularly uninspired geological specimen. A laboratory-grown synthetic SiC [monocrystal](/Monocrystal) – because nature, apparently, can't be bothered to produce enough of this stuff.

